    <note>Wang(2) Ping [1856] His ancestors were Taiyuan jun Wang(2). They then moved to Henan, and subsequently at the end of the Tang, his fifth generation ancestor fled from Guangzhou, Gushi xian to Fuzhou, Houguan xian and served in the administration of the kingdom of Min. His sons moved to Yingzhou, Ruyin xian where Ping was buried. One son, Hui [3958], was a friend of Wang(2) Anshi [1762]. Ping's wife was Zeng(1) Gongliang's [8136] sister. Hui's wife was also a Zeng(1) Shi. Another son, Jiong [3940], was the son-in-law of Jia(3) Changchao's [8031] younger brother, Changqi [3217]. XCB, 159.4b; Xia Song, WJ, 2.5a; Hu Su, WJ, 37.1a-7a; Sanshan zhi, 26.10a; Zeng Gong, WJ, 42.13b, 45.1a-2a (wife, born Zeng, who died in 1078 at age of 79); Wang Anshi, WJ, 93.962-3, 98.1007-8. CBD, 1, 108.</note>
